“I like the idea that the barbershop is sort of a hub of the community: where people can gather, they can talk to each other, and just sort of check in on each other.” Shawn, Master Barber and Owner of Otis & Finn, is helping steer his establishment to be more than just a barbershop. Whether it’s throwing Pride parties or just getting to know new folks, Shawn has created a space that helps the community and has fun while doing it.

Watch the newest episode of H’ead Spaces, where we profile barbershops and get to the root of what makes them, well, them. Thank you to @otisandfinnbarbershop for having us!

Video by @yoyoorick 

#HarrysHeadspaces #HarrysNotTheSame

latestIgtvVideos.title: Stride With Pride
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
We wanted to look back at our Stride With Pride journey and give a big shout out to the folks (@jamie_windust @iam.muse @chiquitettas @iamwestdakota @javiermofficial) that made it happen. We’ve never been prouder to follow along and learn about the places that hold such important meaning. 

Be sure to check out all of the videos in our IGTV series: Stride With Pride 🌈

latestIgtvVideos.title: Stride With Pride: Javier Munõz
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Javier (@javiermofficial) takes us through the West Village in NYC—the storied and historic neighborhood—where as much as things have changed, the area holds true to its strong ties with the LGBTQ community. Follow along as Javier takes us through the intersections of his teenage years. 

#StrideWithPrideHarrys

latestIgtvVideos.title: Stride With Pride: West Dakota
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Drag queen, artist, and organizer West Dakota (@iamwestdakota) takes us to @therosemontnyc in Brooklyn where they got her start as a performer. ✨ Follow West along and find out what makes The Rosemont so special.

#StrideWithPrideHarrys

latestPosts.caption:
We’re proud to launch the #GotYour6 Challenge, our latest initiative to support Veteran mental health.

At Harry’s, we’ve been supporting mental health for the past 6 years by donating over $2M and reaching more than 175,000 veterans and their families. Now, we’re asking you to show veterans that we’ve got their backs.

From July 6th to 20th, we’re donating up to $300K to incredible orgs doing the work on the ground, including: @bwforg @headstrongproject @onetribefoundation @stopsoldiersuicide @teamrwb 💪

Every rep you post helps us get there. Let’s show up for those who’ve served: swipe for instructions on how to participate, and tap the link in bio to learn more!

latestPosts.caption:
Introducing the #GotYour6 Challenge with our co-founder Jeff here to break it down 💪

From July 6 to July 20, for every video you share doing 6 reps of any exercise, Harry’s will donate $6 to organizations supporting Veteran mental health. We’re proud to be partnering with incredible folks at @bwforg @headstrongproject @onetribefoundation @stopsoldiersuicide @teamrwb ❗️

How to participate:
🎥 Record yourself doing any 6 reps (pushups, pullups, squats, you name it!)
🏷️ Use #GotYour6 + your branch tag (like #ArmyGotYour6) in your caption!
👊 Nominate 3+ friends to take the challenge and post

Let’s rep it out and show up for our veterans! Tap the link in bio or check out our pinned post to learn more + enter.

Behind every number is a real person who needs care and support. That’s why we partner with The Trevor Project to help make mental health resources more accessible for the LGBTQ+ community.

Explore resources and support for mental health by visiting the link in bio 🔗
